1
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:30,280
[Sunshine of My Life]

2
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:32,900
[Episode 2]

3
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:06,740
Why are you here?

4
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:10,990
I wanted to ask you why you were here.

5
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:12,810
Did you mail me my sketchbook?

6
00:02:12,810 --> 00:02:15,530
- Not yet.
- But you clearly promised me the other day!

7
00:02:15,530 --> 00:02:19,300
I did promise you, but did I say which day I'd return it?

8
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:22,600
You're playing word games with me! Why are you like this?

9
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,960
Let me ask you something.

10
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:26,130
Why?

11
00:02:26,130 --> 00:02:29,310
No, no, no. Ask, ask, ask! Go ahead and ask.

12
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:32,620
When you were evaluating the red-crowned crane design,

13
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:35,510
why did you replace some of the drawnwork silk with organza?

14
00:02:35,510 --> 00:02:39,390
Because using organza makes the whole outfit feel more ethereal.

15
00:02:39,390 --> 00:02:43,020
Reducing the drawnwork makes it better overall.

16
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:46,250
Not bad.

17
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:50,680
How do you know my evaluation?

18
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:53,960
You eavesdropped on me?!

19
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:57,640
Although I'm a very low profiled businessman,

20
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:00,720
I don't deserve you associating me with "eavesdropping."
 (T/N: wordplay - eavesdropping is composed of two characters, one of which means "stealing" which isn't good for business)

21
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:04,410
- How did you know—
- I'm an honest person and will definitely do what I promised.

22
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:06,190
As to why I didn't send it to you,

23
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:09,740
it is because the phone number you left me was missing a digit.

24
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:12,200
Take a look.

25
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,010
[Mo Fei 1821701605]
(T/N: China's phone numbers should be composed of 11 digits)

26
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,980
Sorry.

27
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:24,420
T-This is right.

28
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:26,590
I'm truly sorry.

29
00:03:28,550 --> 00:03:30,230
Hello?

30
00:03:33,330 --> 00:03:36,240
My pig brain...

31
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,360
How does he know my evaluation?

32
00:03:47,230 --> 00:03:52,060
Brother Xuan, someone saw Lu Zhu at Cayman, and she saw Fang Xiaoyu.

33
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:56,610
She said she wanted to enter a competition to be a model trainee.

34
00:03:59,230 --> 00:04:01,090
- Let's go to Cayman.
- Okay.

35
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:17,960
- Lu Zhu.
- Yeah?

36
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:20,710
Say, you're back in Shanghai but you're not going home.

37
00:04:20,710 --> 00:04:24,310
If Auntie finds out, I won't be able to explain it.

38
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:26,790
What's there to explain?

39
00:04:26,790 --> 00:04:29,060
What is it? Are you afraid my aunt's going to misunderstand?

40
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,720
Don't worry. She knows me.

41
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:34,450
My standard for guys isn't that low.

42
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:38,130
Ha. Ha. Ha.

43
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:40,840
President Tang! President Tang!

44
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:43,080
Cousin?

45
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,930
Come home with me.

46
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:48,810
I still have to have dinner with Brother Xiaoyu.

47
00:04:51,260 --> 00:04:53,170
Want to take your cousin home?

48
00:04:53,170 --> 00:04:56,150
Well, my sister's been missing for three years.

49
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:58,730
I'd like to take her home, too.

50
00:04:58,730 --> 00:05:01,120
When will I be able to do that?

51
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:08,590
I don't want to waste time on you. Come out.

52
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:18,950
Go back with him. I'll meet with you another time.

53
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:21,000
- Then, call me.
- Okay.

54
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:34,180
Auntie!
(T/N: paternal)

55
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,450
Zhu Zhu?

56
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:38,850
Are you surprised? It's unexpected, isn't it?

57
00:05:38,850 --> 00:05:40,470
You're really back?

58
00:05:40,470 --> 00:05:45,260
When your brother called to tell me you were coming back, I didn't believe it. Why did you suddenly come back?

59
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:49,600
Mom, you guys chat first.

60
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,020
Come, come, sit.

61
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:55,350
Did your cousin scold you?

62
00:05:55,350 --> 00:05:57,740
Even if he really scolded me, then everything would be fine.

63
00:05:57,740 --> 00:06:02,180
Do you know? He didn't say anything since he picked me up.

64
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,480
He's too scary.

65
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:07,970
You're getting bolder and bolder now, not saying anything and coming back. You didn't even come home.

66
00:06:07,970 --> 00:06:12,020
It was because I was afraid he'd scold me, so I didn't dare come home.

67
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:15,450
I'll call your uncle in a bit and have him come home early.
(T/N: paternal)

68
00:06:15,450 --> 00:06:17,200
What do you want to eat?

69
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,510
Hairy crabs.

70
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,900
- Nanny Wu!
- Yes!

71
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:27,020
Eat slowly. This is all yours.

72
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:29,430
No one even think of stealing it.

73
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,190
Zhu Zhu, it's not a holiday now.

74
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:34,500
Why did you suddenly come back?

75
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:38,100
Say something.

76
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:40,580
Your uncle is asking you something.

77
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:44,330
What's going on?

78
00:06:44,330 --> 00:06:46,950
Our young lady here decided to take a leave of absence from school.

79
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:49,280
Take a leave of absence from school?

80
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:51,470
Why would you take a leave of absence from school?

81
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:56,280
I... I want to be a model trainee at Cayman.

82
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,090
I've already passed!

83
00:06:58,090 --> 00:07:01,910
Do you really want to go to Cayman? Well, you should finish school first.

84
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:04,100
I don't like the major.

85
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:07,370
I really don't like Business Management at all. I want to be a model.

86
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:09,340
What's good about being a model?

87
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:11,640
You need to study well and graduate.

88
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,670
Help your uncle and cousin manage the company in the future.

89
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:16,360
That is a promising future.

90
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:19,890
Indeed, when your cousin and I helped you choose your major, we did have thoughts

91
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:23,150
of you entering the company to help out after graduating.

92
00:07:23,150 --> 00:07:27,440
I really don't like the major and I don't want to manage the company either.

93
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:29,130
I just want to be a model.

94
00:07:29,130 --> 00:07:31,410
You're really being ridiculous.

95
00:07:31,410 --> 00:07:34,830
If the Business Management major could speak, it would say it didn't like you.

96
00:07:34,830 --> 00:07:37,970
How am I being ridiculous? Why can't I be a model?

97
00:07:37,970 --> 00:07:40,890
Why can't I pick the major that I like?

98
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:44,330
Don't drag my future down just because you are at odds with Fang Xiaoyu!

99
00:07:44,330 --> 00:07:47,890
I'm already an adult! I have the right to make decisions about my own life!

100
00:07:47,890 --> 00:07:51,660
Enough, enough. Let's not fight the moment we see each other.

101
00:07:51,660 --> 00:07:54,560
Zhu Zhu, actually, you wanting to be a model

102
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,560
is not a bad thing.

103
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:59,970
Your cousin knows a lot of people in the industry. He can actually talk to some senior people.

104
00:07:59,970 --> 00:08:04,670
When you are on vacation, you can come and have fun. You don't need to take an absence from school.

105
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:07,200
Have fun? I'm really not here to have fun.

106
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:11,140
I want to be a model. I want to be a professional model. A world-famous supermodel.

107
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:14,370
It's not impossible for you to become a world-famous supermodel.

108
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:17,850
If there were child supermodels, I would be the first to recommend you.

109
00:08:17,850 --> 00:08:21,510
What do you mean by that? Can't I have my own dream?

110
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:23,780
That's right! You only care about your own well-being.

111
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:26,230
Since I was young, you've arranged everything for me.

112
00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:30,430
But have any of you asked what I want or what I like?

113
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:34,730
- No one has ever cared about how I felt. I'll go. I'll leave, okay?
- Zhu Zhu.

114
00:08:34,730 --> 00:08:37,490
- I can make my own decision. You guys don't need to bother with me.
- Lu Zhu!

115
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,790
Zhu Zhu!

116
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:41,100
- This child.
- Hurry and go check on that child!

117
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:43,850
Why chase after her? Mom!

118
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,540
Dad, what are you thinking about?

119
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:00,760
How's Zhu Zhu now?

120
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,750
She's just a child throwing a tantrum.

121
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,130
She'll be fine tomorrow.

122
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:07,570
Cayman is considered to be the

123
00:09:07,570 --> 00:09:10,030
leading model agent company in the country.

124
00:09:10,030 --> 00:09:12,360
If Lu Zhu really likes it,

125
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,650
I think it's okay to let her be a trainee.

126
00:09:15,650 --> 00:09:19,560
It's just that Fang Xiaoyu...

127
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:23,650
No matter how much Fang Xiaoyu hates me,

128
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:26,820
I think he's not that close-minded.

129
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:29,540
Say, Lu Zhu with that personality of hers,

130
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:32,060
if we don't let her go,

131
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:34,660
wouldn't she run away from home?

132
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:36,560
That's right.

133
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,740
All right, let's not talk about that for now.

134
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:42,040
I want to discuss something.

135
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:46,350
After acquiring SLC, I want to merge it with Songtang.

136
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:49,760
So that Songtang won't look so bare.

137
00:09:51,590 --> 00:09:54,450
I'm going to say something you might not like to hear.
- Go on.

138
00:09:54,450 --> 00:09:58,360
Within the whole company, Songtang

139
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:02,440
is indeed the subsidiary brand with the worst sales performance.

140
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:05,790
What do you mean?

141
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:10,390
Do you also support ending Songtang?

142
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:33,690
When I was twenty-something, I was a worker at a textile factory.

143
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:38,340
Later on, I went into foreign trade and produced many ready-made clothes.

144
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:41,450
Now we have Mingyuan Group.

145
00:10:41,450 --> 00:10:46,590
You can say that I've gone through many hardships in the clothing industry my entire life.

146
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:50,190
The enterprise I want to make big the most is Songtang.

147
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:55,310
Its craftsmanship, its oriental motifs, and its spirit

148
00:10:55,310 --> 00:10:59,630
are worthy for us who are in this industry to pass down from generation to generation.

149
00:11:01,090 --> 00:11:05,260
But it's a shame, I didn't manage it well.

150
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:09,510
Dad, I know you have invested a lot of effort into

151
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,890
and sacrificed a lot for Songtang.

152
00:11:11,890 --> 00:11:15,000
However, this is a problem that pertains to the times. It's not your fault.

153
00:11:16,130 --> 00:11:18,420
Don't shift the blame.

154
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:22,820
We're the people who guide consumer preferences.

155
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:26,470
Songtang contains oriental motifs. What does it represent?

156
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:29,750
Our ethnic elements. It's international and ever-lasting.

157
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:34,340
So this brand is worth us promoting to the world.

158
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:38,480
Imagine if one day, Mingyuan no longer has Songtang,

159
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:41,870
then where is Mingyuan's spirit?

160
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:44,550
What will be left of Mingyuan?

161
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:48,150
How I see it, it would just be an empty shell.

162
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:05,960
[Xiongying Design Studio]

163
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:28,710
That's about it. There shouldn't be any problems.

164
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:31,660
Will the client be coming later to try it on?

165
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:35,860
Mo Fei, why don't go back first?

166
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:39,390
I'll communicate with the customer. If there are any issues, I'll contact you.

167
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:41,780
I have to see the customer wearing it

168
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:44,830
to make better alterations to suit her.

169
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:47,460
Teacher Pan, my evening gown...

170
00:12:49,390 --> 00:12:52,350
So the client is Bai Xiaoman?

171
00:12:55,550 --> 00:13:01,070
Teacher Pan, how could you find someone with such low standards to make my dress?

172
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:03,060
You want to attend a charity banquet.

173
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:05,390
Mo Fei wants to create a good piece of work.

174
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:08,140
Say, why can't you two use this opportunity

175
00:13:08,140 --> 00:13:10,750
to let go of the prejudices you have for one another?

176
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:14,970
So this outfit is for a charity banquet?

177
00:13:14,970 --> 00:13:16,610
That's right.

178
00:13:16,610 --> 00:13:21,040
My boyfriend is going to take me to the fashion charity banquet this year.

179
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:23,980
What? You didn't expect that, right?

180
00:13:23,980 --> 00:13:27,420
If I knew it was you, I wouldn't have accepted the work.

181
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:30,310
You won't accept it? Well, I don't even want to wear it!

182
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:32,980
Enough, enough. Enough from both of you.

183
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,600
Haven't you argued enough in school?

184
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,090
Even if you didn't argue enough, I've heard enough already.

185
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:42,410
Teacher, can you help me take a look to see if there's anything I need to adjust?

186
00:13:43,270 --> 00:13:45,280
Stop arguing.

187
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:52,180
Let me see the dress you've designed.

188
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,870
Say, this neckline of yours is so high,

189
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:05,080
are you planning to make it into a mask or a head garment?

190
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:08,040
Are you designing for a nun?

191
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:10,790
Being sexy doesn't mean you have to show skin.

192
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:14,880
Besides, models are just tools to showcase clothes.

193
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:18,120
If you can't even do that, then why be a model?

194
00:14:18,950 --> 00:14:20,540
But the problem is,

195
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:24,450
I can't see what's aesthetic about this design.

196
00:14:24,450 --> 00:14:27,550
If you don't want to wear it, then forget it.

197
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:29,330
- Teacher Pan, I'm leaving now.
- Hey!

198
00:14:29,330 --> 00:14:32,570
Don't leave. Aren't you a designer?

199
00:14:32,570 --> 00:14:36,070
Aren't you supposed to help me change or something?

200
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:42,630
I'll try your great design.

201
00:14:43,460 --> 00:14:46,590
When we were in school, you were always arrogant.

202
00:14:46,590 --> 00:14:51,090
Yet aren't you still serving me by helping me get changed now?

203
00:14:54,180 --> 00:14:59,000
Do you need help? If you have a better attitude towards me,

204
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,400
perhaps I can introduce a few clients to you.

205
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:07,900
Even if I'm starving to death, I wouldn't accept your charity. Move aside.

206
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:27,220
[Retro Pockets]

207
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:51,290
The drawing is quite lifelike.

208
00:15:51,820 --> 00:15:57,270
But I no longer smoke anymore.

209
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:59,900
I used to smoke.

210
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:02,360
But I used to smoke...

211
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,690
I used to smoke...

212
00:16:05,850 --> 00:16:08,800
But now I don't smoke anymore.

213
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:12,170
Do you mind if I smoke

214
00:16:12,170 --> 00:16:14,750
Do you mind...

215
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,050
Do you mind...

216
00:16:16,050 --> 00:16:19,810
- Do you mind if I smoke?
- No.

217
00:16:22,250 --> 00:16:23,920
I don't see it.

218
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:30,990
Let me order takeout. I'm a bit hungry.

219
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:33,360
Sister! Sister!

220
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,650
- You're back?
- I've passed.

221
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:35,900
Passed what?

222
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:39,350
Cayman! Modeling!

223
00:16:39,350 --> 00:16:43,380
Congratulations. I'm ordering takeout. Do you want to eat something? I'm ordering fried chicken.

224
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:48,320
I just passed the exam to be a model and you want me to eat fried chicken. Are you trying to take my livelihood away? I'm not eating!
(T/N: wordplay - "fried" sounds like "break")

225
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:50,360
Fine.

226
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,620
I'll order you a beef salad.

227
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:54,470
That's okay.

228
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:58,180
Sister, stop looking at that. Look at me. What's different about me?

229
00:16:58,860 --> 00:17:01,620
What's different?

230
00:17:03,650 --> 00:17:05,320
The Mo Fan in front of you now

231
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:07,140
is not that athlete from before.

232
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:11,640
I'm a rising star amongst male models.

233
00:17:16,290 --> 00:17:19,490
Can't you take a good look at me? Aren't you happy I got in?

234
00:17:19,490 --> 00:17:22,570
It's not that I'm not happy for you.

235
00:17:22,570 --> 00:17:25,080
It's mom.

236
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:28,910
You traitor! You wouldn't betray me, right?

237
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:33,580
Show me respect. Treat me better.

238
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:36,810
Be careful. One day, I might accidentally let it slip.

239
00:17:36,810 --> 00:17:39,290
You dare? I'll have a duel with you today.

240
00:17:39,290 --> 00:17:42,560
Come on, give it a try. Little brat!

241
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:45,270
- You're fighting with your older sister?
- Sister, your phone is ringing!

242
00:17:45,270 --> 00:17:47,730
Try and move again!

243
00:17:47,730 --> 00:17:49,680
- Hello?
- I'm here.

244
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:52,650
Okay. I'll be right down. Bye-bye.

245
00:17:52,650 --> 00:17:54,290
I say, that's fast.

246
00:17:54,290 --> 00:17:55,850
Go quickly. It's your turn today.

247
00:17:55,850 --> 00:17:59,530
